        "action": "Government campaign on how to halt the climate crisis",
        "additional_details": "Recently, I wrote a piece for The Guardian (https://www.theguardian.com/society/2019/sep/18/government-ad-campaign-climate-crisis-brexit-not-deal). I argue that we need a government-sponsored campaign that educates on how to halt the climate crisis. It\u2019s up to the government to launch such a campaign because of its resources and ability to target every household.\r\n\r\nJoshua Curiel",
        "background": "People still know very little about what \u201cclimate crisis\u201d actually means. According to the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP), 84% of 18- to 24-year-olds agree they need more information to learn how to prevent climate breakdown.",
